HEADWORD: Audiphone
<hw>Au"di*phone</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>audire</ets> to hear + Gr. <?/ sound.]</ety> <def>An instrument
which, placed against the teeth, conveys sound to the auditory nerve and
enables the deaf to hear more or less distinctly; a
dentiphone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

